From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Kasiewicz, Marek" <marek.kasiewicz@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 9 Apr 2026 07:33:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ice: e830: do not write TXTIME doorbell during queue start

Writing zero to the TXTIME doorbell register (E830_GLQTX_TXTIME_DBELL_LSB)
during ice_tx_queue_start() triggers a PQM MDD (Malicious Driver Detection)
event 29 on E830 NICs. The TXTIME engine interprets any doorbell write as a
packet submission signal, but at queue-start time no TXTIME descriptors are
posted yet, causing the hardware to flag the event and silently discard all
subsequent TXTIME transmissions (opackets stays at 0).

The regular TX tail register (QTX_COMM_DBELL) needs to be initialized to 0
so the hardware knows the queue is empty, but the TXTIME doorbell serves a
different purpose — it is only meant to be rung when actually submitting
packets with launch timestamps.

The kernel ice driver (ice-2.5.4) does not write to the TXTIME doorbell
during queue setup either — it only assigns the register address for later
use by the TX path.

Remove the ICE_PCI_REG_WRITE(txq->qtx_tail, 0) call from the TXTIME branch
of ice_tx_queue_start(). The pointer assignment is kept so the TX datapath
can ring the doorbell during normal TXTIME packet submission.

Signed-off-by: Kasiewicz, Marek <marek.kasiewicz@intel.com>
---
 drivers/net/intel/ice/ice_rxtx.c | 3 ---
 1 file changed, 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/intel/ice/ice_rxtx.c b/drivers/net/intel/ice/ice_rxtx.c
index 1234567890..abcdef1234 100644
--- a/drivers/net/intel/ice/ice_rxtx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/intel/ice/ice_rxtx.c
@@ -898,9 +898,6 @@
 
 		txq->qtx_tail = hw->hw_addr + E830_GLQTX_TXTIME_DBELL_LSB(txq->reg_idx);
 
-		/* Init the Tx time tail register*/
-		ICE_PCI_REG_WRITE(txq->qtx_tail, 0);
-
 		err = ice_aq_set_txtimeq(hw, txq->reg_idx, 1, ts_elem, ts_buf_len, NULL);
 		rte_free(ts_elem);
 		if (err) {
